# c5dd4e6f67644a0a8045f705e827e862
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:396
msgid ""
"You observe inconsistent behavior when one node obtains an object from "
"another node in the cluster"
msgstr ""

# 0c86be96201e4609ba474665b49aed9a
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:398
msgid ""
"As part of the initial system preparation, you must synchronize the "
"clocks on all nodes in your cluster. Minor time differences do not cause "
"problems, but differences of more than a few minutes can affect Traffic "
"Server operation."
msgstr ""

# 705a80ed24c44708bafac6f1cbdc188b
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:403
msgid ""
"You should run a clock synchronization daemon such as xntpd. To obtain "
"the latest version of xntpd, go to `<http://www.eecis.udel.edu/~ntp/>`_."
msgstr ""

# 927f4c80737a4f84948d3101890e2163
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:407
msgid "Web browsers display an error document with a 'data missing' message"
msgstr ""

# 239276c4541a4b0791011784b9bc8f73
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:409
msgid "A message similar to the following might display in web browsers: ::"
msgstr ""

# 8ba8bf0d6e654fd09bd6fd24c37829a2
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:415
msgid ""
"This is a Web browser issue and not a problem specific to (or caused by) "
"Traffic Server. Because Web browsers maintain a separate local cache in "
"memory and/or disk on the client system, messages about documents that "
"have expired from cache refer to the browser's local cache and not to the"
" Traffic Server cache. There is no Traffic Server message or condition "
"that can cause such messages to appear in a web browser."
msgstr ""

# 967901e1976a4ffda860155f4f0eb0c4
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:423
msgid "Traffic Server does not resolve any websites"
msgstr ""

# 6e4a2bb663c64fbeab208aaf34fdb1d0
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:425
msgid ""
"The browser indicates that it is contacting the host and then times out "
"with the following message: ::"
msgstr ""

# f1ca82adeabf47ecae28f4173e858e9f
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:430
msgid ""
"Make sure the system is configured correctly and that Traffic Server can "
"read the name resolution file:"
msgstr ""

# c29f1118b0c140b68bd9dada8fbf844f
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:433
msgid ""
"Check if the server can resolve DNS lookups by issuing the nslookup "
"command (for example, ``nslookup www.myhost.com``)."
msgstr ""

# 4c535b309b4d40d193cf5d2bfe2dbabc
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:435
msgid ""
"Check if the :manpage:`resolv.conf(5)` file contains valid IP addresses "
"for your DNS servers."
msgstr ""

# aadbf1caef7c49698765271a131c58cb
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:437
msgid ""
"On some systems, if the :manpage:`resolv.conf(5)` file is unreadable or "
"has no name server entry, then the operating system uses ``localhost`` as"
" a name server. Traffic Server, however, does not use this convention. If"
" you want to use ``localhost`` as a name server, then you must add a name"
" server entry for ``127.0.0.1`` or ``0.0.0.0`` in the "
":manpage:`resolv.conf(5)` file."
msgstr ""

# b350e45a11e846e5966887b22bb72fa7
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:443
msgid ""
"Check that the Traffic Server user account has permission to read the "
":manpage:`resolv.conf(5)` file. If it does not, then change the file "
"permissions to ``rw-r--r--`` (``644``)."
msgstr ""

# da456c4f134246adaad24b7872116e66
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:448
msgid "'Maximum document size exceeded' message in the system log file"
msgstr ""

# 22ed6588749b4976ac848d9ae5024d56
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:450
msgid "The following message appears in the system log file: ::"
msgstr ""

# 5f472846a224434ebe1077882bbc82d3
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:454
msgid ""
"A requested object was larger than the maximum size allowed in the "
"Traffic Server cache, so Traffic Server provided proxy service for the "
"oversized object but did not cache it. To set the object size limit for "
"the cache, modify the :ts:cv:`proxy.config.cache.max_doc_size` variable "
"in the records.config file. If you do not want to limit the size of "
"objects in the cache, then set the document size to ``0`` (zero)."
msgstr ""

# 6a92fe1bffd24d6a8ac3c2c7a87215f7
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:463
msgid "'DrainIncomingChannel' message in the system log file"
msgstr ""

# 3865b08cc2e244b69ccc6503a7ec91e7
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:465
msgid "The following messages may appear in the system log file: ::"
msgstr ""

# 3c87fe85ec6c49ca8c28442c11c49177
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:471
msgid ""
"These error messages indicate that a browser is sending HTTP requests to "
"one of the Traffic Server cluster ports, either ``rsport`` (default port "
"8088) or ``mcport`` (default port 8089). Traffic Server discards these "
"requests. This error does not cause any Traffic Server problems. The "
"misconfigured browser must be reconfigured to use the correct proxy port."
" Traffic Server clusters should ideally be configured to use a separate "
"network interface and cluster on a private subnet, so that client "
"machines have no access to the cluster ports."
msgstr ""

# caa73a092843498abbaec8383fda6f4b
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:481
msgid "'No cop file' message in the system log file"
msgstr ""

# b70136b5fd8c4ad1adf56d716488fe75
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:483
msgid "The following message appears repeatedly in the system log file: ::"
msgstr ""

# f0f792608e634d48b1afd3316f35e929
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:487
msgid ""
"The file ``var/trafficserver/no_cop`` acts as an administrative control "
"that instructs the :program:`traffic_cop` process to exit immediately "
"without starting :program:`traffic_manager` or performing any health "
"checks. The ``no_cop`` file prevents Traffic Server from starting "
"automatically when it has been stopped with the option:`trafficserver "
"stop` command. Without this static control, Traffic Server would restart "
"automatically upon system reboot. The ``no_cop`` control keeps Traffic "
"Server off until it is explicitly restarted with: ::"
msgstr ""

# b68f1ec48c17492e8bab7d776ed6a50b
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:499
msgid "Warning in the system log file when manually editing vaddrs.config"
msgstr ""

# 54b716d89ee145e9aba2a0eff4f3b63f
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:501
msgid ""
"If you manually edit :file:`vaddrs.config` as a non-root user, then "
"Traffic Server issues a warning message in the system log file similar to"
" the following::"
msgstr ""

# ddec9a372dbd4f74a43e7e02eebedf64
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:507
msgid ""
"You can safely ignore this message as Traffic Server will still apply "
"your configuration edits."
msgstr ""

# cdd224161d284b5f9719de2364b16cb5
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:511
msgid "Traffic Server is running but no log files are created"
msgstr ""

# 980ff04de99b4fc3a1687cebbd61542f
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:513
msgid ""
"Traffic Server only writes event log files when there is information to "
"record. If Traffic Server is idle, then it's possible that no log files "
"exist."
msgstr ""

# 126265fba8c1442e8c78a6239aba357d
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:517
msgid ""
"If Traffic Server is not idle, and you still do not see log files being "
"generated, verify the following:"
msgstr ""

# abf81352c47f4f759667c92de4a8621d
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:520
msgid ""
"Make sure you're looking in the correct directory. By default, Traffic "
"Server creates log files in the ``logs`` directory. This can be modified "
"by changing :ts:cv:`proxy.config.log.logfile_dir` in "
":file:`records.config`."
msgstr ""

# ca3094aa9f5c40b7b5e1f3e7d0d967ce
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:524
msgid ""
"Check that the log directory has read/write permissions for the Traffic "
"Server user account. If the log directory does not have the correct "
"permissions, then the :program:`traffic_server` process will be unable to"
" open or create log files."
msgstr ""

# b8f5749673f44099be0d44abf21b916f
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:529
msgid ""
"Check that logging is enabled by checking the value of the "
":ts:cv:`proxy.config.log.logging_enabled` variable in "
":file:`records.config`."
msgstr ""

# 8b78989d3301409bad17d97525fc7148
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:532
msgid ""
"Check that a log format is enabled. In :file:`records.config`, select the"
" standard or custom format by editing variables in the Logging Config "
"section."
msgstr ""

# 508a21449ee4488cab8b01c600e4406c
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:537
msgid "Traffic Server shows an error indicating too many network connections"
msgstr ""

# 19550345c12c47eebd0b3a79b85f6c3c
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:539
#, python-format
msgid ""
"By default, Traffic Server supports 8000 network connections. Half of "
"this number is allocated for client connections and the remaining half is"
" for origin server connections. A *connection throttle event* occurs when"
" either client or origin server connections reach 90% of half the "
"configured total limit (3600 by default). When a connection throttle "
"event occurs, Traffic Server continues processing all existing "
"connections but will not accept new client connection requests until the "
"connection count falls below the limit."
msgstr ""

# 1d46dde512754a65a9761b018851fc67
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:548
msgid "Connection throttle events can occur under the following conditions:"
msgstr ""

# 975c18b802594620b451ce70c3e4e80e
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:554
msgid "Connection Spike"
msgstr ""

# 0e21abb59adc4167b8c17d8153223996
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:551
msgid ""
"Too many client requests (enough to exceed your configured maximum "
"connections) all reach Traffic Server at the same time. Such events are "
"typically transient and require no corrective action if your connection "
"limits are already configured appropriately for your Traffic Server and "
"origin resources."
msgstr ""

# 7cb042385b504656aca89c39088e6b84
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:560
msgid "Service Overload"
msgstr ""

# 7c8860199f444b0da3f449b4c953e143
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:557
msgid ""
"Client requests are arriving at a rate faster than that which Traffic "
"Server can service them. This may indicate network problems between "
"Traffic Server and origin servers or that Traffic Server may require more"
" memory, CPU, cache disks, or other resources to handle the client load."
msgstr ""

# e4e29b58001e4f8e8f3ecb387a1a1523
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:562
msgid ""
"If necessary, you can adjust the maximum number of connections supported "
"by Traffic Server by editing "
":ts:cv:`proxy.config.net.connections_throttle` in :file:`records.config`."
msgstr ""

# 71a00fa644ec44e3bab69107a00cde65
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:568
msgid ""
"Do not increase the connection throttle limit unless the system has "
"adequate memory to handle the client connections required. A system with "
"limited RAM might need a throttle limit lower than the default value. Do "
"not set this variable below the minimum value of ``100``."
msgstr ""

# b284577e3f4c423792faad0a322ebd4a
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:574
msgid "Low memory symptoms"
msgstr ""

# f2ab53bb82184f288841df5a5c3e9d46
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:576
msgid ""
"Under heavy load, the Linux kernel can run out of RAM. This low memory "
"condition can cause slow performance and a variety of other system "
"problems. In fact, RAM exhaustion can occur even if the system has plenty"
" of free swap space."
msgstr ""

# a0abb56456d34f49b495da0f467d36eb
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:581
msgid ""
"Symptoms of extreme memory exhaustion include the following messages in "
"the system log files (``/var/log/messages``)::"
msgstr ""

# 110c77ad7eb540a388baf52f4dc74ec3
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:590
msgid ""
"To avoid memory exhaustion, add more RAM to the system or reduce the load"
" on Traffic Server."
msgstr ""

# 1471fdeaef1b49a4be5fbb86ba2936a2
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:594
msgid "Config checker"
msgstr ""

# fea3e1a9118247b2a5efa476a643fb5e
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:596
msgid ""
"Traffic Server supports the below command to validate the config offline,"
" inorder to allow the config to be pre-checked for possible service "
"disruptions due to synatx errors::"
msgstr ""

# fcb46c0e16b540dbac0aff78d7bc2eb1
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:601
msgid "<config_dir> is the location of the config files to be validated."
msgstr ""

# f5c9b2f4c45349b19bb642e17f77df6a
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:604
msgid "Connection timeouts with the origin server"
msgstr ""

# 4a06e462ba1a49d1a05afda7fc30a23f
#: ../../appendices/faq.en.rst:606
msgid ""
"By default, Traffic Server will timeout after 30 seconds when contacting "
"origin servers. If you cannot avoid such timeouts by otherwise addressing"
" the performance on your origin servers, you may adjust the origin "
"connection timeout in Traffic Server by changing "
":ts:cv:`proxy.config.http.connect_attempts_timeout` in "
":file:`records.config` to a larger value."
msgstr ""

